VIRUS EXPERT 1.60 (A)


This is an old killer by Paul van der Valk (Holland?), and is updated by a
guy from Poland. It was realesed autum '90,  with a little better check of
the first  executable in the  startup. Yet, it's quite good IF you can get
your hands on the actual viruses yourself, because the program itself does
not know ANY virus at all!!! It uses a library, called VirusExpert.Library
which contains a few (if any) viruses.  The library is not attached to the
Libs: directory on the (hard)disk, but must be placed in the root. I don't
think there  ever was a standard library  with it, all the  libraries I've
seen was made by different  users, who recorded  some of the  viruses into
the library.  (Order a special  HEADER library  from Erik?)  Although some
viruses can't be  recogniced by TVE, because they hide as standard BB! TVE
has a GREAT bootblock analyze function built in, the best ever seen yet!!!


IN THIS TEST:
The number  indicates the Virus Rating,  which means how  dangerous is the
virus.  Secondly there might  be a S and/or a F,  which means  that it can
spread to other disks (S), or format other disks (F).

@endnode

