Viruscope is not able  to find ANY of the bombs, and misses  quiet many of
all the rest, including bootblocks. When Viruscope finds a NON STANDARD BB
you would probably leave it in the believe  that Viruscope couldn't find a
virus.  But here you should try the DECODE gadget. A analyse function will
then display a message telling what Viruscope thinks about that BB. An odd
thing happened when I tested it for The Lamer Exterminator II 2:  First it
was announced as  a NON STANDARD BB,  so I entered DECODE.  Then Viruscope
