FIDESPROF 3.12 (L)   

This  is  a new viruskiller from Spain, yet it has been developed over the
past  couples  of  years.   I consider this release (version 3.12) as some
sort  of  a  preview,  because the bugs are numerous, and quiet often very
annoying  when  appearing.  In the document is stated, that a previous bug
was removed from this version.  The bug appeared if the default was set to
check  DH0:  at start, and there in fact wasn't a harddisk connected.  Yet
this version asks for volume DH0:  when started the first time.  If a disk
is  inserted  with  a  virus that FidesProf doesn't recognise, a requester
will  show  up,  asking  for  volume  DF156 for instance.  Volumes such as
DF22:, DF48:, DF197:  and a lot more is among them.

I guess this is some remains that the author uses to determine the viruses
in  his  own library, or something like that.  Another very annoying thing
is,  that there's still a lot of spanish text in the program.  Even though
we  used  a  english  version  for  this test.  Small bugs here and there,
gadgets  that  does  nothing or contains spanish text, a strange brainfile
and it's configuration.  All these things makes this kil- ler quiet odd to
use,  but not impossible!  Actually is it pretty good to find the viruses,
except  for the linkfile-viruses.  Hopefully there will be an update soon,
with  a little better english version of the program and the document.  It
has  the  great  features  that  are  required in a good killer today.  It
handles  all  available  RAM's  and  drives well, and I had no GURU's like
those described in the document.  Keep it up, John!

@endnode

