FIND'EM'ALL 5.1 (M) 

This viruskiller  is not listed above,  because it isn't a regular program
like BootX  or ZeroVirus.  It's a small command, and it  only pops up once
and then disappear  again, something like VMK.  It has two features in it:


A BOOTBLOCK INSTALLER, which installes disks with a FEA bootblock. This BB
can (says the author anyway) check  ALL kinds of vectors and libraries for
ANY changes there may  occour. A lot of (not yet  used by viruses) vectors
are checked, (I believe it was over 500!) so there should be a fair chance
to detect a virus in MEMORY.  FindEmAll is NOT able to  examine bootblocks
or files for viruses,  but it is able to recognise what happens in MEMORY!

A VECTORCHECKER COMMAND, with lot's of technical  stuff, but it would pro-
bably be difficult for a regular AMIGA user to identify what is virus, and
what is not.  I guess that if you use the  FEA bootblock on DOS disks, you
are pretty sure of not being infected with anything. (Except a cold!?)
I have only used it in about 20 days, but it sure looks promising too.
As a supplement to other killers, of course!

@endnode
